When customers have exported an existing SF cluster ARM template and are attempting to add a new secondary certificate.  New-AzureRmResourceGroupDeployment I get errors about a missing 'certificateStore' parameter for the virtualMachineScaleSets resource

 they may see the error


Exporting the template from the portal currently has a bug where the "certificateStore" property is stripped out, thus cx will see an error about this missing property when they try to redeploy

When exported the secrets in the osProfile section appears like this:
"virtualMachineProfile": {
                    "osProfile": {
                        "computerNamePrefix": "[parameters('virtualMachineScaleSets_sednode_name')]",
                        "adminUsername": "sedwardsrdp",
                        "windowsConfiguration": {
                            "provisionVMAgent": true,
                            "enableAutomaticUpdates": true
                        },
                        "secrets": [
                            {
                                "sourceVault": {
                                    "id": "[parameters('virtualMachineScaleSets_sednode_id')]"
                                },
                                "vaultCertificates": [
                                    {
                                        "certificateUrl": "https://sedsfeastkeyvault0002.vault.azure.net:443/secrets/sedsfeast0002/fa7232239e344c6d807780c3d873fcd4"
                                    }
                                ]
                            },

However note the "vaultCertificate" is only showing the certificateUrl, it should also include the "certificateStore"

                                   "vaultCertificates": [
                                    {
                                        "certificateUrl": "https://sedsfeastkeyvault0002.vault.azure.net:443/secrets/sedsfeast0002/fa7232239e344c6d807780c3d873fcd4",
                                        "certificateStore": "My"
                                    }
                                ]
